    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>CoKu Tau-Aur 4 is a young stellar system consisting of a near equal-mass, close binary and a circumbinary disk. As in similar systems via the gravitational interactions between the binary and the disk, a gap is opened in the disk. The size of the gap was estimated via modeling, however direct measurements of it is currently not available. Using the current model of the system, we can show that ALMA can resolve the inner gap in the circumbinary disk. Using Band 6 continuum measurements, we will be able to directly determine the size of the gap, which is currently unknown. We also want to observe a CO transition, which will allow us to constrain the inclination of the system. The ALMA observations will help us to repeat and revise the previous radiative transfer modeling of the system, including more realistic wall properties and more constraints on the shape of the gap. The latter being linked to the orbital parameters of the binary would help us to derive the eccentricity of the binary.</prp:abstract>
